         <abstract id="aspace_bbfa5f48c059f0c6019a237a3bc56b20">The collection consists of blotters, daybooks, journals, and ledgers relating to the general store of Timothy Green and Richard Green in East Haddam, Connecticut. The firm was later known as Green and Smith, Green and Pratt, and F. W. Green and Co. Also included are materials concerning the sloop <title render="italic">
               <part>Amelia</part>
            </title>, the schooner <title render="italic">
               <part>Russell</part>
            </title>, and the ship <title render="italic">
               <part>Indiana</part>
            </title>.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <corpname rules="aacr" source="local">
               <part>Green and Smith Company</part>
            </corpname>
         </origination>
    
